
🪄 Type Registry Examples for Wishful

These examples show how to register complex types so the LLM
can generate functions that return properly structured data.


===================================
Example 1: Simple Type Registration
===================================


Generated book: Book(title='The Left Hand of Darkness', author='Ursula K. Le Guin', year=1969, isbn='9780441478125')
Type: <class 'wishful.static.library.Book'>

================================
Example 2: Typed Function Output
================================


Parsed profile: UserProfile(name='John Doe', email='john@example.com', age=30, is_active=True)
Name: John Doe
Email: john@example.com
Age: 30

==============================================
Example 3: Multiple Functions with Shared Type
==============================================


Parsed product: {'name': 'Laptop', 'price': 999.99, 'in_stock': True, 'category': 'Electronics'}
Created product: {'name': 'Mouse', 'price': 29.99, 'in_stock': True, 'category': 'Accessories'}

===============================
Example 4: Nested Complex Types
===============================


Extracted contact: ContactInfo(name='Alice Smith', phone='555-1234', email='alice@example.com', address=Address(street='123 Main St', city='Springfield', state='IL', zip_code='62701'))
Lives in: Springfield, IL

================================
Example 5: Types with Validation
================================


Age validation result: Person(name='Validated Person', age=25)
Birth year calculation: Person(name='Born in 1995', age=30)

